detaileddescription.para: Handles the action when "Back" button is pressed. It navigates back to the "Home Screen" view.
Handles the action when "Add Fonction" button is pressed. It adds a new function to the system if it does not already exist.
Handles the action when "Delete Fonction" button is pressed. It deletes a function from the system if it exists.
Handles the action when "Add User" button is pressed. It adds a new user to the system if it does not already exist.
Handles the action when "Delete User" button is pressed. It deletes a user from the system if it exists.
Handles the action when "Change Fonction" button is pressed. It updates the user's function in the system.
Handles the action when "Change Password" button is pressed. It updates the user's password in the system after validation.
Handles the change of user in the "User for change fonction" combobox. It updates the displayed function to match the selected user's current function.
Handles the action when "Save Rate" button is pressed. It updates the exchange rate in the system.
Clears the error label after a certain delay.

parameterdescription.para: The error label to be cleared.

detaileddescription.para: The Settings class is responsible for managing the settings view of the application. It provides functionalities to manage functions, users, user roles, and to update passwords.
